	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hiyas everyone... Ive been looking to get one of these amulets for awhile... I'm a 53 magician.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;  I've gone on three fear raids, each time, one of these dropped.  It kinda breaks my heart when I'm the ONLY int caster that needs and somehow, a rogue walks away with it.  What was Verant thinking, making a very nice caster be able to be clicked from ones inventory?  Why dont they do that with *useful* melee items?  Maybe its kinda hard for you troll warriors out there to relate, so I will give an example.<br>    So you are on a naggy raid and the cloak of flames drops... you are gareenteed it... since, by some bizaare reason, you are the only tank there.  But little do you, the casters decide to roll on it... and guess who wins it? A nuke-happy wizard.  Yeah, he will sure get good use out of it.<br>    Now you see how casters feel?  Please.. reach out to your guild.  Stop the wrong-doing.  Together, WE CAN make a difference.<br><br>Tyme Telzal<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
